$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Meta niġu għall-kodifikazzjoni binarja, Hexadecimal huwa aktar effiċjenti minħabba li jnaqqas 8 ċifri għal 2. Barra minn hekk, Hex jipprovdi grad akbar ta &#39;densità ta&#39; informazzjoni u preċiżjoni ogħla fin-numri milli jagħmel binarju. Dan huwa dovut għall-fatt li Hex juża 16-il simbolu minflok tnejn biss bħal binarji. Minħabba din l-effiċjenza akbar, Hexadecimal huwa spiss użat meta kodifikazzjoni binarja fl-informatika u elettronika diġitali kif ukoll għall-applikazzjonijiet tax-xjenza tal-kompjuter.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Barra minn hekk, Eżadeċimali jieħu inqas spazju minn deċimali. B&#39;żewġ ċifri biss minflok 8 ċifri binarji, in-numri Hex jirrappreżentaw numri kbar b&#39;mod ħafna aktar konċiż. Dan jista &#39;jkun ta&#39; għajnuna kbira meta taħdem ma &#39;sistemi tal-kompjuter, peress li hemm inqas ċans għal żbalji meta tikteb kodiċi hex meta mqabbla ma&#39; kodiċi deċimali li għandhom daqstant punti deċimali madwar il-post kollu!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = 'X&#39;inhi l-firxa ta&#39; valuri li jistgħu jiġu rappreżentati b&#39;Hexadecimal?';
