$lang['When it comes to decoding Hexadecimal, there are a few things you need to know. First, just like the decimal system, the hexadecimal system has 10 symbols (0-9) that represent numbers. However, in hexadecimal, these digits have values that are twice as large as their counterparts in the decimal system. So, while the number “10” is represented by the symbol “A” in hexadecimal, it would be equal to “10” in the decimal system.'] = 'Meta niġu għad-dekodifikazzjoni Hexadecimal, hemm ftit affarijiet li għandek bżonn tkun taf. L-ewwel, bħas-sistema deċimali, is-sistema eżadeċimali għandha 10 simboli (0-9) li jirrappreżentaw in-numri. Madankollu, b&#39;eżadeċimali, dawn iċ-ċifri għandhom valuri li huma d-doppju tal-kontropartijiet tagħhom fis-sistema deċimali. Għalhekk, filwaqt li n-numru &quot;10&quot; huwa rappreżentat bis-simbolu &quot;A&quot; f&#39;eżadeċimali, ikun ugwali għal &quot;10&quot; fis-sistema deċimali.';
$lang['Similarly, after reaching 9 in Hexadecimal (represented by “F”), we start counting again at 10 (“10”). This pattern continues until we reach 15 (“1F”), at which point we reset back to 0 and begin counting again at 16 (“20”). This might sound confusing at first, but with a little practice, it will become second nature!'] = 'Bl-istess mod, wara li nilħqu d-9 f&#39;Hexadecimal (rappreżentati minn &quot;F&quot;), nerġgħu nibdew ngħoddu f&#39;10 (&quot;10&quot;). Dan il-mudell ikompli sakemm nilħqu 15 (&quot;1F&quot;), f&#39;liema punt irrisettjaw lura għal 0 u nerġgħu nibdew ngħoddu f&#39;16 (&quot;20&quot;). Dan jista &#39;ħoss konfuż għall-ewwel, iżda bi ftit prattika, se ssir it-tieni natura!';
