$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Tista &#39;tuża eżadeċimali biex tikkonverti bejn valuri deċimali u binarji. Pereżempju, il-konverżjoni ta&#39; 10011011001010 f&#39;eżadeċimali tirriżulta f&#39;0x4F. Dan ifisser li l-valur 4F jirrappreżenta n-numru binarju 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Fil-matematika u x-xjenza tal-kompjuter, eżadeċimali (ukoll bażi 16, jew hex) hija sistema numerika pożizzjonali b&#39;radix, jew bażi, ta&#39; 16. Juża sittax-il simbolu distint, ħafna drabi s-simboli 0–9 biex jirrappreżentaw valuri żero sa disgħa, u A, B, C, D, E, F (jew alternattivament a–f) biex jirrappreżentaw valuri minn għaxra sa ħmistax. Pereżempju, in-numru eżadeċimali 2AF3 huwa ugwali, f&#39;deċimali, għal (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , jew 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Kull ċifra eżadeċimali tirrappreżenta erba &#39;ċifri binarji (bits) (imsejħa wkoll &quot;nibble&quot;), u l-użu primarju ta&#39; notazzjoni eżadeċimali huwa bħala rappreżentazzjoni faċli għall-bniedem ta &#39;valuri kodifikati binarji fl-informatika u l-elettronika diġitali. Pereżempju, il-valuri tal-byte jistgħu jvarjaw minn 0 sa 255 (deċimali) iżda jistgħu jkunu rappreżentati b&#39;mod aktar konvenjenti bħala żewġ ċifri eżadeċimali fil-medda 00 sa FF. Eżadeċimali huwa wkoll komunement użat biex jirrappreżenta l-indirizzi tal-memorja tal-kompjuter.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex hija abbrevjazzjoni ta &#39;Hexadecimal, li hija bbażata fuq struttura bażi -16 u tintuża biex tissimplifika kif l-istruzzjonijiet għall-kompjuters huma rappreżentati. Din is-sistema tan-numri ta &#39;16-il simbolu ġiet żviluppata bħala mezz ta&#39; inibizzjoni ta &#39;numru binarju ta&#39; 8-bit, sabiex id-dejta tista &#39;tiġi kodifikata fil-kompjuters mingħajr sforz. Jista &#39;jiġi stampat u ttajpjat bl-użu ta&#39; żewġ ċifri hex differenti b&#39;kull ċifra hex turi nibble jew forsi format ta &#39;4-bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Din is-sistema tan-numri tuża 16-il simbolu li huma rappreżentati f&#39;medda minn 0-9 jew AF. L-0–9 jirrappreżentaw numri sa disgħa filwaqt li AF huwa rappreżentat mill-10–15 numeriku. Meta mqabbla mat-tliet tipi l-oħra ta&#39; sistemi tan-numri, is-sistema numerika eżadeċimali hija meqjusa bħala l-aktar waħda effettiva.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Il-kodiċi eżadeċimali tiegħek mhux validu';
